dog potty train help i need help with my dog he wont use the pads you can put on the floors and they poop and pee on it well he pees on it but wont poop on it instead he uses the carpet and sometimes when i take him outside i am out there with him for like half an hour but he dont use the restroom and by the time we come in the house he poops please help me how do i get him to use the pad or go outside help confinement a crate or a leash can be used to restrict the movements of your pet dog since the restricted space in which your dog is allowed to move will become his personal space he will take care not to dirty it when he feels the urge to pee or poop he will then give you indications such as feeling restless going round in circles sniffing the ground etc training you could effectively potty train your dog using a leash a leash will help you keep a vigil at your dog and his actions without a leash a dog may get distracted in other stuff around him but just with a gentle tug of the leash his attention can be brought back to what you are trying to teach him timing be consistent in your training and devote enough time to train your dog schedule his walks such as soon after he wakes up just before he goes to bed after every meal and so on doing so will help your pet understand the time table that is set for him to urinate and defecate praise words of encouragement are necessary for your dog too if he does things correctly and as required do not forget to praise him praising your dog will encourage him to do the right thing time and again to win your love and affection Housebreaking Toilet humour Toilet Crate training Urinary incontinence Dog agility Obedience training RuneScape quests Pitaten Milton H. Erickson Hamster Prayer Shaggy dog story Fancy rat The Death Gate Cycle Humphrey Bogart Fecal incontinence Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Laika Dog Shit Care Bears Aerial (dance move) Falconry Garfield Traumatic incident reduction Fasting Rule of St Benedict USS America